The paper proposes a new deep feature selection method based on deep architecture, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on a specific precision medicine problem, which suggests that it could belong to the computational biology (cs.CE) sub-category. The proposed method uses stacked auto-encoders for feature representation, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses deep learning to identify significant risk factors, which suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
